dlgPiSramMibRevMajor.name: dlgPiSramMibRevMajor
dlgPiSramMibRevMajor.description: The Major Revision level. A change in the major revision level represents a major change in the architecture of the MIB. A change in the major revision level may indicate a significant change in the information supported and/or the meaning of the supported information, correct interpretation of data may require a MIB document with the same major revision level.

dlgPiSramMibRevMinor.name: dlgPiSramMibRevMinor
dlgPiSramMibRevMinor.description: The Minor Revision level. A change in the minor revision level may represent some minor additional support. no changes to any pre-existing information has occurred.

dlgPsStatsEnableMask.name: dlgPsStatsEnableMask
dlgPsStatsEnableMask.description: Statistics Collection Enable mask. This mask enables or disables all statistics defined in this MIB. 0 - Disables statistics collection. 1 - Enables statistics collection. 2 - Clear existing statistics (resets all stats to zero) Default value is 1 - statistics collection enabled

dlgPsPollingInterval.name: dlgPsPollingInterval
dlgPsPollingInterval.description: The Agent's polling interval in seconds. This is the length of time that the Agent will keeps stats within the Current Stats group. By default, this value is 3600 seconds (1 hour). At the end of each interval the statistics are reset to zero and the counters begin counting up again. The dlgPsElapsedTime variable provides an indication how long into the current interval the agent has been collecting statistics.

dlgPsElapsedTime.name: dlgPsElapsedTime
dlgPsElapsedTime.description: Number of Elapsed seconds since the start of the current polling interval.

dlgPsCurrentInterrupts.name: dlgPsCurrentInterrupts
dlgPsCurrentInterrupts.description: Number of hardware interrupts generated by Span or D4x based boards for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentDrvCommands.name: dlgPsCurrentDrvCommands
dlgPsCurrentDrvCommands.description: Number of commands sent to the driver for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentFWCommands.name: dlgPsCurrentFWCommands
dlgPsCurrentFWCommands.description: Number of commands sent to the Firmware for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentUnSolEvents.name: dlgPsCurrentUnSolEvents
dlgPsCurrentUnSolEvents.description: Number of unsolicited events from the Firmware for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentBytesRead.name: dlgPsCurrentBytesRead
dlgPsCurrentBytesRead.description: Number of bytes read from the Firmware during record for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentBytesWritten.name: dlgPsCurrentBytesWritten
dlgPsCurrentBytesWritten.description: Number of bytes written to the Firmware during playback for the current interval.

dlgPsCurrentLostMsgToFW.name: dlgPsCurrentLostMsgToFW
dlgPsCurrentLostMsgToFW.description: Number of lost messages (commands) to the Firmware for the current interval. This value should always be zero. A non zero value typically indicates a Firmware or hardware failure.

dlgPsCurrentLostMsgFromFW.name: dlgPsCurrentLostMsgFromFW
dlgPsCurrentLostMsgFromFW.description: Number of lost messages (events) from the Firmware for the current interval. This value should typically be zero. A non zero value indicates the host cannot service all the messages being generated by the firmware.

dlgPsCurrentFWErrorMsgs.name: dlgPsCurrentFWErrorMsgs
dlgPsCurrentFWErrorMsgs.description: Number of error message packets generated by the Firmware for the current interval. This should typically be zero.

dlgPsCurrentDrvErrorMsgs.name: dlgPsCurrentDrvErrorMsgs
dlgPsCurrentDrvErrorMsgs.description: Number of error message packets generated by the Driver for the current interval. This should tpyically be zero.

dlgPsTotalInterrupts.name: dlgPsTotalInterrupts
dlgPsTotalInterrupts.description: Total Number of hardware interrupts generated by the Span or D4x based boards.

dlgPsTotalDrvCommands.name: dlgPsTotalDrvCommands
dlgPsTotalDrvCommands.description: Total Number of commands sent to the driver.

dlgPsTotalFWCommands.name: dlgPsTotalFWCommands
dlgPsTotalFWCommands.description: Total Number of commands sent to the Firmware.

dlgPsTotalUnSolEvents.name: dlgPsTotalUnSolEvents
dlgPsTotalUnSolEvents.description: Total Number of unsolicited events from the Firmware.

dlgPsTotalBytesRead.name: dlgPsTotalBytesRead
dlgPsTotalBytesRead.description: Total Number of bytes Read from the Firmware during record.

dlgPsTotalBytesWritten.name: dlgPsTotalBytesWritten
dlgPsTotalBytesWritten.description: Total Number of bytes written to the Firmware during playback.

dlgPsTotalLostMsgToFW.name: dlgPsTotalLostMsgToFW
dlgPsTotalLostMsgToFW.description: Total Number of lost messages (commands) to the Firmware. This value should always be zero. A non zero value typically indicates a Firmware or Hardware failure.

dlgPsTotalLostMsgFromFW.name: dlgPsTotalLostMsgFromFW
dlgPsTotalLostMsgFromFW.description: Total Number of lost messages (events) from the Firmware. This value should typically be zero. A non zero value indicates the host cannot service all the messages being generated by the firmware.

dlgPsTotalFWErrorMsgs.name: dlgPsTotalFWErrorMsgs
dlgPsTotalFWErrorMsgs.description: Total Number of error message packets gernerated by the Firmware. This should typically be zero.

dlgPsTotalDrvErrorMsgs.name: dlgPsTotalDrvErrorMsgs
dlgPsTotalDrvErrorMsgs.description: Total Number of error message packets generated by the Driver. This should typically be zero.
